Senate Government Operations 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB2228
Jackson
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2228* House Bill No. 2533
by deleting Section 11 and substituting instead the following:
SECTION 11. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-3004(i), is amended by
deleting "An LEA" wherever it appears in the subsection and substituting "An LEA or public
charter school", by deleting "an LEA" wherever it appears in the subsection and substituting "an
LEA or public charter school", and by deleting "the LEA" wherever it appears in the subsection
and substituting "the LEA or public charter school".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting Section 39 and substituting the following:
SECTION 39. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-2302(a), is amended by
deleting "school board" in subdivisions (a)(1) and (2) and substituting "local board of education
or public charter school governing body".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting Section 59 and substituting the following:
SECTION 59. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-16-213, is amended by deleting
subsection (b) and substituting:
(b) In addition to the intervention options available under § 49-1-602, if a virtual
school is identified as a priority school pursuant to § 49-1-602, then the LEA must not
exceed its enrollment cap specified in § 49-16-211(b) and the virtual school identified as
a priority school must not exceed its enrollment for the prior year. The enrollment cap
takes effect for the school year immediately following the identification and does not
affect students enrolled in the virtual school at the time of the identification.
(c)
SA0529
013860
- 1 -

(1) If a virtual school is identified as a priority school pursuant to § 49-1-
602 for two (2) consecutive cycles, then the LEA must close the virtual school for
the school year immediately following the identification.
(2) Notwithstanding chapter 3, part 1 of this title, if a virtual school is
closed pursuant to this subsection (c), then the Tennessee investment in student
achievement formula (TISA) payments for the LEA that established the virtual
school must exclude a student who was a member in the virtual school in the
prior school year who did not remain a member in the LEA.
(3) If a virtual school is closed pursuant to this subsection (c), then:
(A) Within one (1) calendar week of the closure decision, the
virtual school must notify in writing the parents or legal guardians of all
students enrolled in the virtual school of the closure decision;
(B) Within thirty (30) days of the closure decision, the department
of education must communicate to the parents or legal guardians of all
students enrolled in the virtual school of other schools or educational
options in which the student is eligible to enroll;
(C) The virtual school must not enroll any new students; and
(D) A contracted nonprofit or for-profit provider of the virtual
school must not withhold student records from the LEA or the school to
which a virtual school student transfers.
AND FURTHER AMEND by adding a new section immediately preceding the antepenultimate
section and renumbering the subsequent sections accordingly:
SECTION __. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-16-214, is amended by deleting
the section and substituting:
(a) An establisher may contract for services with nonprofit and for-profit
providers for the operation and management of a virtual school.
- 2 - 013860

(b) The department of education shall maintain and publish on the department's
website a list of providers that operated or managed a virtual school pursuant to
subsection (a) that was closed pursuant to § 49-16-213(c)(1).
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting "rules promulgated by the state board of education" in
subdivision (b)(2)(B) in the amendatory language of Section 67 and substituting "chapter 6, part
45 of this title".
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting Sections 60 through 63 and Section 69 and renumbering
remaining sections accordingly.
